The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Q amp;A

 Mutual benefit

 I have invested Rs 10,000 in UTI Dividend Yield Fund in July this year. Will this be eligible for tax deduction under section 80C? Are all types of mutual fund investments eligible for this tax deduction? 

 B. Hari, Calcutta

 No, your investment in UTI Dividend Yield Fund shall not be qualified for deduction under section 80 C. Investments only in the specified mutual funds known as equity-linked savings scheme (ELSS) are eligible for the deduction.

 No relief

 Can the amount of savings put in Kisan Vikas Patra within the limit of Rs 1 lakh be deducted from total income for calculating income tax for 2005-06?

 Hari Sankar Kakati, Kamrup

 vestment in Kisan Vikas Patra is not eligible for tax deductions under section 80C.

 Learning the ropes

 I am employed and also pursuing an MBA course. I believe that individuals get a tax benefit for paying tuition fees of their wards. Am I eligible for any relief for the payment of my tuition fees?

 Amitabha Bhowmick, by e-mail

 No, the benefit is available only for payment of tuition fees of the assessees children. However, you can claim benefit for repayment of any education loan, which you might have taken for your course.

 When death strikes

 In case of accidental death, what additional documents does one need to submit in addition to the ones needed for a death claim?

 S. K. Lamba, Ranchi

 addition to the requirements for a death claim, the claimant should submit all the reports, including police, hospital and others, pertaining to the accident as required by the company.

